Take a quick glance of this case study and analysis.


What kind of problem are we solving, what is the story?

  • Were exploring a marketing claim for Blueprinty, a software firm specializing in tools for developing patent blueprints. The goal is to show that using Blueprintys software increases the success rate of patent approvals. This study forms part of a project for the UC San Diego, MSBA program; MGTA 495 - Marketing Analytics course.

What is the goal of the analysis?

  • The analysis aims to identify if theres a significant correlation between using Blueprintys software and the number of patents awarded to these 1,500 firms over the last 5 years. The analysis will provide insights into the effectiveness of Blueprintys software in increasing patent approvals and will help guide marketing strategies by identifying the most effective methods for promoting the software to potential clients.
